On 8/12/10 9:50 AM, Ewa Bartosiewicz wrote:
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Ok, I think I found a lot of information in the developer&#39;s manual, but
&gt; I have a very primary question: where do I get the heritrix source code,
&gt; where I can put my module? The .tar.gz I loaded contains only binary and
&gt; no source...
&gt;
&gt; thanks for your help!
&gt;
&gt; Ewa
&gt;
&gt; --- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com
&gt; &lt;mailto:archive-crawler%40yahoogroups.com&gt;, Gordon Mohr &lt;gojomo@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; There is no bundled component for doing so, but it should be easy to
&gt;  &gt; write, either in Java or one of the scripting languages Heritrix
&gt; supports.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; You don&#39;t mention which version you&#39;re using, so I&#39;ll assume Heritrix
&gt;  &gt; 3.0.0+ (&quot;H3&quot;).
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Every processor may optionally have its own DecideRule (or more
&gt;  &gt; usefully, set of rules via something like DecideRuleSequence), called
&gt;  &gt; &#39;shouldProcessRule&#39;. If changed from the default (an always-ACCEPT
&gt;  &gt; rule), and the rule returns REJECT, the Processor&#39;s normal activity will
&gt;  &gt; be skipped.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Thus, adding rules to whatever Processor is doing your content-writing
&gt;  &gt; such that they REJECT uninteresting content will have the desired effect.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; Rules are passed the CrawlURI instance, which for any successful fetch
&gt;  &gt; includes ways to access the retrieved content as either an InputStream
&gt;  &gt; or a CharSequence. Rules may be written in Java or via the
&gt;  &gt; ScriptedDecideRule class, supplied with their behavior by any JSR-223
&gt;  &gt; scripting engine. Javascript (aka ECMAScript), Beanshell, and Groovy
&gt;  &gt; should always be available as options in our standard distribution;
&gt;  &gt; adding JRuby or Jython or Clojure shouldn&#39;t be hard.
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; - Gordon @ IA
&gt;  &gt;
&gt;  &gt; On 7/29/10 9:21 AM, e.bartosiewicz wrote:
&gt;  &gt; &gt; I&#39;m trying to do a crawl using Heritrix, but I can&#39;t find one
&gt; crucial module which would be able to filter the content of the fetched
&gt; pages before writing them into the archive. I need to write only the
&gt; pages that contain given keywords. Is that possible? Am I going to have
&gt; to write something myself? How can I write my own filter for Heritrix?
&gt;  &gt; &gt;
&gt;  &gt; &gt;
&gt;  &gt; &gt; Thanks for any help in this matter!
